===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[epocha]]'' < Greek ''epokhe''

===Noun===
'''epoch''' (''plural'' '''[[epoches]]''')
# A particular [[period]] of history, especially one considered remarkable or noteworthy. 
# A notable event which marks the beginning of such a period.
# (''astronomy'') A precise [[instant]] of time that is used as a [[reference]] point.


====Synonyms====
*''a particular period in history:'' [[era]]; [[age]]

====Translations====
*Bulgarian: [[епоха]] (epoha) ''f''
*[[Polish]]: epoka ''f''
*Portuguese: [[época]] ''f''

